quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  109,1,"Say: “O unbelievers!”"{1},footnotes:1:1
  109,2,"I do not worship those that you worship"{1},footnotes:1:1
  109,3,"neither do you worship Him Whom I worship;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  109,4,"nor will I worship those whom you have worshipped;"
  109,5,"nor are you going to worship Him Whom I worship."{1},footnotes:1:1
  109,6,"To you is your religion, and to me, my religion."{1},footnotes:1:1
  110,1,"When the help comes from Allah, and victory (is granted),"{1},footnotes:1:1
  110,2,"and you see people entering Allah's religion in multitudes,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  110,3,"then extol the praise of your Lord and pray to Him for forgiveness. For He indeed is ever disposed to accept repentance."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  111,1,"Destroyed were the hands of Abu Lahab, and he lay utterly doomed."{1},footnotes:1:1
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor his acquisitions."{1},footnotes:1:1
  111,3,"Surely, he will be cast into a Flaming Fire"
  111,4,"along with his wife, that carrier of slanderous tales;"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  111,5,"upon her neck shall be a rope of palm-fibre."{1},footnotes:1:1